feature.name: Text phone/TTY compatibility
feature.description: This device is a textphone/TTY for the deaf, or a CapTel phone. These are landline phones that display conversations as text.

feature.name: Visual Alerts - Incoming Calls
feature.description: This device displays a visual alert for incoming call, such as a flashing light, the caller’s name or caller's photo, if it is stored in your contact list.

feature.name: High Contrast Mode
feature.description: This device comes with at least one high contrast mode.

feature.name: Automatic Answer
feature.description: This device can answer calls straight away without you having to do anything.

feature.name: Flat Back for Table Top Operation
feature.description: The back of this device is flat, so you can lie it on a table or other flat surface to use without having to hold the phone.

feature.name: Physical Dialling Keys
feature.description: This device has physical keys (not a touchscreen) which are easy to press.

feature.name: Copy and Paste
feature.description: You can use copy and paste on this device.

feature.name: GPS
feature.description: You can track your location with this device using its GPS.

feature.name: Photo Telephone List
feature.description: You can add photos of people with their numbers in your telephone book (called “contacts” in your phone).

feature.name: Screen Timeout Disabled
feature.description: This device will allow you to take as long as you want to press buttons or type a response, stopping the screen from going blank or locking the device if you do not use the device for a period of time. The screen will only be turned off or locked by pressing the "off" button.

feature.name: Simple Instructions
feature.description: This device uses simple language on the screen for instructions and messages.

feature.name: Simple Reminders
feature.description: This device uses simple language for alerts and reminders.

feature.name: Voice Notes
feature.description: You can record short voice notes, save them and play them back later.

feature.name: Allows for sign language communication
feature.description: This device supports sign language chat using video communication, at a minimum of 30 frames per second, which is the required video quality.

feature.name: Bluetooth or Wi-Fi
feature.description: This device can connect to other devices or accessories using Bluetooth or Wi-Fi.

feature.name: Front Facing Camera
feature.description: This device has a camera that faces you, so you can lip read, sign or video call someone else and they can see you.

feature.name: Text Messaging/SMS
feature.description: You can send and receive text messages.

feature.name: Vibrating Alerts - Adjustable
feature.description: This device allows users to select different vibration settings for various notifications

feature.name: Video Communications - Two-way
feature.description: You can make video calls where you can see the other person and they can see you, using your Wi-Fi or mobile data.

feature.name: Battery Alert - Audible
feature.description: This device will make a sound to tell you when the battery is running out or when it is recharging.

feature.name: Brightness Adjustable
feature.description: You can adjust the brightness of the display to make it easier to read.

feature.name: Power Cue
feature.description: This device gives you a cue such as a sound or vibration when you press the power on/off button, so you know it has been pressed.

feature.name: Screen Reader
feature.description: This device will read text to you from the screen, and allow use by people without vision.

feature.name: Text Size Adjustable
feature.description: You can make the text on the display larger or smaller to make it easier to read.

feature.name: Voiced Menus
feature.description: This device will read the menu options to you.

feature.name: Messaging Options - Email
feature.description: You can send and receive email.

feature.name: Messaging Options - IM
feature.description: You can send and receive ‘instant messenger’ (IM) messages.

feature.name: Messaging Options - MMS
feature.description: You can send and receive multimedia messages, which can include photographs, audio and video clips.

feature.name: Predictive Text
feature.description: This device helps you write text messages more quickly by guessing the words from the first few letters you type.

feature.name: SMS Personalisation and Reuse
feature.description: You can create and store standard text messages that you can quickly select and send to anyone without having to retype them each time. For example, “I’m in a meeting, I’ll call you back”.

feature.name: Headset - plug connected
feature.description: This device lets you listen and talk during a phone call without needing to hold the phone, by plugging in a headset with earbuds/headphones and a microphone.

feature.name: Speaker-phone option
feature.description: This device can be used in loud speaker mode during a call, without having to hold it close to your ear.

feature.name: Switch control option
feature.description: This device can be used in loud speaker mode during a call, without having to hold it close to your ear.

feature.name: Voice Recognition for Accessing Features
feature.description: You can activate features by speaking commands into the phone, reducing the need to use the keypad or touchscreen.

feature.name: Voice Recognition for Dialling
feature.description: You can call someone in your contacts list by speaking the person’s name.

feature.name: Additional Instructions
feature.description: This device gives you extra help with instructions.

feature.name: Simplify Display
feature.description: You can make the display only show the things you need.

feature.name: Closed Captioning
feature.description: This device can show closed captioning (CC) where it is available in a video (e.g. YouTube) or video stream

feature.name: Hearing Aid Microphone Coupling
feature.description: This device reduces buzzing interference when using the device with the Microphone on hearing aids or cochlear implants. This is called Hearing aid compatibility (HAC) for hearing aid and cochlear implant users, and is rated as M3 or M4.

feature.name: Braille Display Support
feature.description: This device can be connected with a braille display.

feature.name: Dictation / Speech-to-Text
feature.description: This device can convert what you say into text, including converting punctuation.

feature.name: Key Numbers - Standard Layout
feature.description: This device has the number keys which are laid out in the standard way with 1 2 3 at the top and * 0 # at the bottom.

feature.name: Key Press - Vibration or Click
feature.description: This device has a vibration option to let the user know that a key or function has been pressed on the touchscreen of the device e.g. dialling a number, typing a text message, and some other controls. Phones with physical press buttons will provide a "click" to let the user know that a key has been pressed.

feature.name: Screen Magnifier
feature.description: This device has an option to zoom in to parts of the screen to make the display larger, including when you are using the internet.

feature.name: Text Style Adjustable
feature.description: You can change the style of the text (font) on the screen, which may make it easier to read.

feature.name: Voice Control /Personal Assistant
feature.description: This device can help you carry out functions by giving the device voice commands e.g. writing and sending texts, placing phone calls, scheduling events, posting social media updates, searching and surfing the internet, opening different applications etc. This may be called a personal assistant, virtual assistant, voice control etc.

feature.name: Stylus or Prosthetic Device support
feature.description: You can press buttons or use the touchscreen with a pointing device, stylus or prosthetic device (a prosthetic device is an artificial device that serves as a replacement for a body part).

feature.name: Voice Control / Personal Assistant
feature.description: This device can help you carry out functions by giving the device voice commands e.g. writing and sending texts, placing phone calls, scheduling events, posting social media updates, searching and surfing the internet, opening different applications etc. This may be called a personal assistant, virtual assistant, voice control etc.

feature.name: Hearing Aid Telecoil Coupling
feature.description: For hearing aid users in telecoil (T switch) mode, this device reduces buzzing (interference) from the device to the hearing aid. This is called Hearing aid compatibility (HAC) for hearing aid and cochlear implant users, and is rated as T3 or T4.

feature.name: Personalised Shortcuts
feature.description: You can assign a feature or task to a single key or a short key sequence.

feature.name: Lanyard Option
feature.description: This device is made to have a strap or lanyard attached.

feature.name: Key Marker – Raised '5'
feature.description: This device has a raised dot or bump on the number ‘5’ key, so you can find it by touching it.

feature.name: Guarded/Recessed Keys
feature.description: This device has individual keys that are recessed or guarded in some way to reduce the chance that you will press the wrong key.

feature.name: Automatic Redial
feature.description: This device can keep calling (redial) a busy or unavailable number until you get through.

feature.name: Gesture Based Navigation
feature.description: You can use simple gestures (hand movements) to enter text or navigate your device (e.g., Back, Home).

feature.name: Flicker Free Display
feature.description: The screen of the tablet does not flicker at a rate that could cause problems for people with photo-epilepsy (between 2 Hz and 60 Hz).

feature.name: Visible Focus Indicators
feature.description: This device provides a visual cue of the active area of the device screen. An example is a blinking cursor in a text box on an online form.

feature.name: Reduced hand movement option
feature.description: This device has alternative ways to use/control the device that do not involve pinching or twisting your fingers

feature.name: Voice amplification
feature.description: This device makes your voice louder for the person at the other end to hear you better.
